# 1848

label rel_1848_danish_war:
    scene black with fade
    centered "{b}{size=40}The Crisis in the North{/size}{/b}\nApril 1848 - Schleswig-Holstein" with dissolve
    pause 1.0

    scene bg prussia office

    show schleswig sad at left
    show schleswig sad with vpunch

    "Schleswig bursts into your office, knocking over an inkwell."

    sw "Helpppppp!"

    show prussia normal at right

    p "I swear by the Iron Cross, if you ruined my Krupp artillery requisition forms..."
    
    show holstein frustrated at center
    
    h "It's Denmark! That bi- she's trying to annex Schleswig!" 
    h "She's marching troops right up to the border!"

    sw "I-I thought things were going better with her... she said she'd leave me forever and cancel the personal union!"

    h "You have to do something! You're the biggest military power in the Confederation!"
    
    show prussia smug

    p "That Denmark needs to learn her lesson! I've had enough of her bullying you two!"

    p "If Copenhagen wants to test the temper of my steel, I am more than happy to oblige. Consider the vanguard mobilized."
    
    "Schleswig and Holstein look at you with absolute adoration as you casually sign the mobilization orders."
    
    scene bg schleswig battlefield with fade
    
    "April 1848. The fields of Jutland."
    
    show prussia intense
    
    p "General Wrangel! Push the infantry past the Danewerk! I want the Danish defenses crushed before sundown!"
    p "Let's remind her who holds the true power in the North!"
    
    "Your armies smash through the Danish lines with terrifying efficiency."
    "The Danish forces are routed at the Battle of Schleswig. Your troops march triumphantly deep into Jutland by August, occupying the territory."
    
    show holstein joyful at left
    show schleswig joyful at right
    
    h "You did it! You actually pushed them back!"
    sw "We're safe! Oh, Prussia, you are magnificent on the battlefield!"
    
    show prussia joyful at center
    
    p "Hmph. It was barely a warm-up."
    p "Let's march on Copenhagen and finish this!"

    show holstein at offscreenleft
    
    "Before you can issue the order, a courier rides into the command tent, his horse foaming at the mouth."
    
    show prussia frustrated
    
    p "What is it!? Can't you see I'm busy manifesting my destiny!?!??"
    
    "The courier hands you two sealed letters. One bears the crest of the British Royal Navy. The other, the two-headed eagle of the Russian Tsar."
    
    show prussia serious
    
    "You break the seals and read them."
    "The air in the tent suddenly grows freezing cold."
    
    p "...The Tsar is massing troops on my eastern border. He demands I withdraw immediately."
    p "And the British are threatening to blockade my entire coastline if the Baltic balance of power is upset."
    
    show schleswig intense
    
    sw "Wait... what does that mean?"
    
    show prussia frustrated
    
    p "Bah!!!! I can't fight a two-front war against the Great Powers!"
    
    show prussia intense
    
    p "Wrangel! Halt the advance! Send an envoy to Malmö. Tell the Danes we will sign an armistice."
    
    h "But... the Frankfurt Parliament! They ordered you to secure our total freedom!"
    
    p "The Parliament has no army. I do. And I am not sacrificing Berlin to the Russians for a couple of farms in Jutland."
    p "The war is over. I saved you from annexation, but I am not conquering Denmark today."
    
    scene bg negotiation room

    uk "Right. Well. If everyone has had a chance to review the terms... perhaps we can move forward with the signing?"
    
    show denmark smug at right
    
    dk "I am perfectly happy with the terms. A complete withdrawal of Prussian troops from Schleswig and Holstein. As it should be."
    
    show prussia frustrated at left
    
    p "Wipe that smirk off your face, Denmark. We both know my artillery shattered your lines at the Danewerk. You didn't win this war."
    
    dk "And yet, here you are, signing a surrender. Funny how that works, isn't it?"
    
    show prussia intense
    
    p "I swear, if we were in that field right now, I would—"
    
    "A heavy, gloved hand slams onto the table, rattling the inkwells."
    
    show russia intense at center
    
    ru "Enough."
    ru "You will not threaten the Danish crown, little eagle. The Tsar has decreed that the Baltic balance of power remains unchanged. Or do I need to march two hundred thousand men across the Vistula to remind you?"
    
    show britain intense at right
    hide denmark
    
    uk "Quite right. The Royal Navy is currently holding its position just outside your ports, Prussia."

    uk "We simply cannot have a unified German state controlling both sides of the Danish straits. It's bad for trade. Sign the paper, be a good girl, and we'll sail the fleet home."
    
    show prussia frustrated
    
    "You grind your teeth so hard your jaw aches. Your blood is boiling, screaming at you to draw your sword."

    "However, your navy consists of a few glorified fishing boats. Your industry is not enough. A two-front war against the British blockade and the Russian army means total annihilation."
    
    show prussia intense
    
    p "Fine. But let the record show I am doing this for the stability of Europe, not because I recognize Danish authority over the duchies."
    
    show britain smug
    
    uk "Let the record show whatever makes you feel better, dear. Just sign the document."
    
    "You snatch the quill, aggressively signing your name to the Armistice of Malmö."
    
    show prussia normal
    
    p "There. Are you happy? My troops will pull out by the end of the week."
    
    show russia normal
    
    ru "A wise decision. See that they do."
    
    "Russia and Britain collect the documents, acting like you are nothing more than a misbehaving child they just scolded."
    
    jump turn_start

label rel_1848_bavaria_scandal:
    scene black with fade
    centered "{b}{size=40}The Lola Montez Affair{/size}{/b}\nMay 1848 - Munich, Bavaria" with dissolve
    pause 1.0
    scene beerhall
    show bavaria drunk at right

    b "A-and then... *hic*... she demanded a title! A title!"

    show prussia neutral at left

    p "Just breathe, Bavaria. Here, drink some water."

    show bavaria sad

    b "She wasn't even Spanish, Prussia! She was just an Irish actress named Eliza! And my King... my King!... threw away the entire crown for her!"
    
    b "The university was rioting! The streets were on fire! Over a fake flamenco dancer!"

    show prussia frustrated

    p "Yeah, that's... definitely one way to lose a throne..."

    p "I brought you some schnapps, by the way. Let's just slide this over here..."

    "You push a heavy glass across the table. Bavaria immediately downs it and buries her face in the table."

    show bavaria drunk

    b "Austria is going to make fun of me forever. The whole Confederation is laughing at me..."

    show prussia normal

    p "Hey... Half the continent is on fire right now..."
    
    show prussia joyful

    p "If your biggest problem is a messy royal scandal, you're actually doing great."

    show bavaria embarrassed

    b "You're... you're not going to make fun of me?"

    show prussia smug

    p "Oh, I'm definitely gonna make fun of you later, just not today."

    p "Austria is too busy yelling at people in the Frankfurt Parliament to care about you right now anyway."

    "Bavaria sniffles, reaching out to grab your sleeve."

    show bavaria drunk

    b "You're actually a pretty good friend when you aren't trying to militarize my borderssss..."

    p "Don't push it. Now drink your water before you pass out on my boots."

    "You spend the rest of the evening acting as emotional support, earning her trust while Austria is completely distracted."

    jump turn_start

label rel_1848_baden_rebellion:
    scene black with fade
    centered "{b}{size=40}Part II: The Hecker Rebellion{/size}{/b}\nLate April 1848 - The Grand Duchy of Baden" with dissolve
    pause 1.0

    scene bg prussia office with fade
    
    "You are deep in the middle of auditing the quarterly coal yields from the Ruhr when the heavy oak doors of your office are practically thrown off their hinges."
    
    show baden embarassed at left
    
    bw "Prussia! You have to deploy the army! Right now! Drop the paperwork!"
    
    show prussia neutral at right
    
    p "Good morning to you too, Baden. I see we are skipping pleasantries today."
    
    show baden sad
    
    bw "There is absolutely no time for pleasantries! Friedrich Hecker just declared a Republic in Konstanz!"
    bw "He's seized the armories! He's marching north through the Black Forest with thousands of armed men!"
    
    show prussia frustrated
    
    p "Ugh. Again? I thought we put down the riots in March."
    
    bw "This isn't a riot, it's an organized march! He has thousands of armed radicals heading north!" 
    bw "My Grand Duke is having a complete breakdown, my ministers are packing their bags to flee to Switzerland, and the Frankfurt Parliament is just sitting around debating the definition of human rights instead of sending help!"
    
    show prussia neutral
    
    "You slowly close your logistics folder, letting out a long, exhausted sigh."
    
    p "And your own state troops? The garrisons you are supposed to maintain?"
    
    bw "They're defecting or fleeing! The civil administration is completely breaking down!" 

    show baden with vpunch

    bw "They want to dismantle my entire government and reorganize the state, and I don't have the manpower to stop them!"

    p "Take a deep breath, Baden. These are romantic poets and university students. I will show them what a professional military actually looks like."
    
    scene black with fade
    "A few days later..."
    
    scene bg field with fade
    
    "You manage to rapidly deploy your infantry all the way to the southern edge of Germany, utilizing the rail networks you've fought so hard to fund."
    "At the town of Kandern, your forces finally intercept the republican militia."
    "You stand on a ridge overlooking the valley. Below, the radical militia charges down the hills, singing revolutionary songs and waving the black-red-gold flag. They have numbers, and they have passion."
    
    show baden nervous at left
    show prussia intense at right
    
    bw "There's so many of them... are you sure your lines will hold?"
    
    show prussia smug
    
    p "Passion is a wonderful thing, but it does not hold a line against grapeshot."
    
    show prussia intense
    
    p "First rank! Present arms!"
    
    "The Prussian line moves with terrifying precision. The click of hundreds of rifle hammers being pulled back echoes across the valley, a sound entirely devoid of emotion."
    
    p "Fire."
    
    "A deafening crack of volley fire shatters the rebel charge. The hills fill with thick, acrid white smoke."
    "When the smoke clears, the reality of professional warfare has set in. The revolutionaries, realizing that poetry cannot defeat the army with a state, scatter in absolute panic."
    
    scene bg karlsruhe palace with fade
    
    "A few days later, you are standing in the grand halls of Karlsruhe. Order has been brutally and efficiently restored."
    
    show baden joyful at left

    show prussia normal at right
    
    bw "I can't believe it... it's really over. They've dropped their weapons and fled for the Swiss border."
    
    show baden embarrassed
    
    bw "I... I don't know how to repay you, Prussia. The delegates in Frankfurt just wanted to talk about legal theories, but you actually saved my state from total collapse."
    
    show prussia joyful
    
    p "You don't need to repay me with coin. Just remember who kept your borders intact when the foundations started shaking."
    
    show prussia normal
    
    p "Now, if you'll excuse me, I need to go audit the ammunition my infantry spent. Bullets don't pay for themselves."
    
    "You leave Baden staring after you in absolute awe."

    bw "So cool..."
    
    jump turn_start

label rel_1848_mecklenburg_date:
    scene bg field
    
    "You take a brief carriage ride out of the city to the Baltic coast, seeking refuge from the endless screaming and burning barricades."
    
    "You find Mecklenburg standing in the middle of a massive, sun-drenched wheat field, happily chewing on a piece of straw."
    
    show mecklenburg joyful at right

    mv "Thank you for visiting, Prussia. I'm sorry it's not very exciting here."
    
    show prussia joyful at left
    
    p "Mecklenburg, 'exciting' is currently trying to burn down my palace. This is perfect."

    show prussia smug

    p "Do you hear that? Listen closely."

    "Mecklenburg nervously looks around the empty field."

    show mecklenburg embarrassed

    mv "I... I just hear the wind. And maybe a cow."

    p "Exactly. No gunfire. No parliamentarians demanding constitutions. Just absolute, glorious silence."

    show mecklenburg normal 

    p "I have to say, I am incredibly impressed with your discipline. While the rest of the Confederation is throwing a massive, collective temper tantrum, you haven't had a single proper riot."

    show mecklenburg embarrassed

    mv "Oh, well... it's not really discipline. We just don't have enough paved roads for a proper mob to march on."
    
    mv "And the peasants are too spread out with the harvest to read any of those liberal pamphlets..." 
    
    mv "It's mostly just dirt and feudalism up here... we're a bit behind the times..."

    show prussia serious

    p "Don't sell yourself short!"

    show prussia normal

    p "While everyone else is busy writing poetry and burning effigies, you're keeping us all fed!"
    
    p "It's highly efficient."
    p "I happen to find efficiency very attractive."

    show mecklenburg embarrassed with vpunch 

    "Mecklenburg's face turns almost as red as a revolutionary flag. She desperately tries to hide behind a bundle of harvested wheat."

    mv "T-thank you..." 

    mv "I'll, um... I'll make sure to keep the grain yields high for you..."

    "You spend a surprisingly peaceful afternoon walking through the fields, enjoying the company of the one state in Germany that isn't on fire."
    
    jump turn_start

label rel_1849_dresden:
    scene black with fade
    centered "{b}{size=40}The May Uprising{/size}{/b}\nMay 1849 - Dresden, Kingdom of Saxony" with dissolve
    pause 1.0

    scene bg prussia office with fade
    
    "The year is 1849. The German states are reeling from the March Revolutions."
    "Saxony rejected the new Frankfurt Constitution, causing her people to absolutely lose their minds and riot in her capital, Dresden."

    scene bg palace interior
    with dissolve

    "Saxony is in her highly cultured living room in Dresden."
    "The same Dresden is currently on fire and riddled with barricades."
    "She's hammering away at the telegraph key in absolute fear..."

    show saxony frustrated at center

    s "AUSTRIA! YOU ARISTOCRATIC COW! ANSWER ME!" 

    show saxony frustrated with vpunch
    s "I KNOW YOU ARE RECEIVING THIS!"

    scene bg comms room 
    show austria frustrated at center
    with hpunch

    a "SAXONY! THIS IS REALLY NOT A GOOD TIME!"

    show hungary frustrated at left

    hu "I WANT A DIVORCE! I’M DECLARING INDEPENDENCE AND I’M TAKING THE TRANSYLVANIA ESTATE!"

    a "HUNGARY PLEASE PUT DOWN THE SWORD... LET’S TALK ABOUT THIS...!" 
    a "Look, I bought you a new corset, we can go to a café..."

    # Quick cut back to Saxony
    scene bg palace interior
    show saxony frustrated at center

    "Saxony yanks the ticker tape, reads it, then furiously types back."

    s "YOU TOLD ME TO REJECT THAT STUPID CONSTITUTION!" 

    s "YOU SAID WE WERE GOING TO MAINTAIN THE OLD ORDER TOGETHER!" with hpunch

    s "WELL MY PEOPLE ARE RIOTING!" 

    s "EVEN MY FAVORITE OPERA COMPOSER IS OUT THERE MAKING BOMBS!" with vpunch

    s "HELP ME!" with hpunch

    # Back to Austria
    scene bg comms room
    show austria intense at left
    show hungary angry at right
    
    show wine at fly_across_screen

    "Austria dodges a flying wine glass, aggressively tapping her telegraph key."

    a "I CAN’T SEND TROOPS TO DRESDEN RIGHT NOW! CAN’T YOU SEE I’M FIGHTING FOR MY LIFE!!??!?!? ASK BAVARIA..."

    # Back to Saxony
    scene bg palace interior
    show saxony sad at center

    s "BAVARIA IS DRUNK AND HIDING UNDER HER BED BECAUSE SHE THINKS FRANCE IS GOING TO CROSS THE BORDER! I NEED YOUR ARMY!"

    "The clicking on Saxony's end stops."
    "(Hungary's saber just cleanly sliced Austria's telegraph wire in half)."

    s "Hello?!"
    show saxony frustrated
    s "Ugh, useless! I am the cultural jewel of Germany, I do not deserve this disrespect!"
    "Suddenly, the stained-glass window shatters. You jump into the room, landing in a perfect three-point superhero pose."
    with vpunch
    show prussia smug at right
    with easeinright

    p "Hola."

    show saxony frustrated at center

    s "Oh, good lord. Why is it you??"

    show prussia intense
    
    p "Shut up. I know you don't like me all that much, but you appear to need some brawn..."

    s "Get out of my house! I’d rather be overthrown by angry democrats than accept help from {i}you{/i}!"

    show prussia joyful
    p "Too late! My glorious troops are already marching down your streets! My artillery will compose a far better tune than whatever that hack Wagner is playing out there!"

    show prussia intense

    p "Now, where were we? Ah, yes. CRUSHING THE INSOLENT REBELS!"

    play sound "sfx/knocking.ogg"
    with hpunch

    "The barricaded door rattles violently. Angry shouting echoes from the hallway."

    show saxony intense at center

    s "They’re breaking through! Prussia, if you actually brought your army, use it!"

    p "Oh, I will. But first, you must admit it."

    s "Admit what?!"

    p "Admit that Austria is a washed-up has-been riding the high of the Congress of Vienna! Admit that {i}I{/i} am the cool one!"

    show saxony frustrated

    s "I will never betray Austria! She’s my best friend!"

    show prussia smug

    p "Very well. Let the anarchists have you. I hear they’re setting up a provisional government. Good luck with the paperwork."

    "The barricades start sliding back as the rioters push harder."

    show saxony intense

    s "Okay! Fine! Austria is a washed-up has-been and your guns are very cool! Just shoot them!"

    show prussia joyful

    p "Heh heh heh... "

    hide prussia 
    with moveoutright

    show saxony normal at center

    s "I am going to need so much therapy..."

    jump turn_start

label rel_1849_palatinate:
    scene black with fade
    centered "{b}{size=40}The Palatine Uprising{/size}{/b}\nJune 1849 - Munich, Kingdom of Bavaria" with dissolve
    pause 1.0

    scene bg palace interior
    with fade

    "The Rhenish Palatinate, a territory belonging to Bavaria but physically separated by the Rhine, has completely rebelled."
    "It has formed a provisional government, and sworn loyalty to the Frankfurt Constitution."

    show bavaria drunk at center
    with vpunch

    b "Why is the Palatinate trying to secede?!!?!?!?!?"

    show bavaria drunk at left_side_sprite

    "Bavaria is drunk as hell, pacing frantically around her office holding a heavy stone stein of schnapps."

    show bavaria drunk at right_side_sprite

    b "First the Lola Montez thinggg... and now this?! I ammmmm a traditional Catholic kingdom! I don't do 'democracy'!"

    show bavaria drunk at left_side_sprite

    show prussia smug at right
    with easeinright

    p "Knock, knock."

    show bavaria frustrated
    with hpunch

    b "Prussia! Who let you in here?! I didn't send for you!"

    show prussia smug

    p "I hear your Palatine citizens are wearing French hats and setting up barricades. Nasty business, revolutions."

    show bavaria sad

    b "It's a nightmare! They're begging France to cross the border and help them!" 
    show bavaria sad with vpunch

    b "If France marches into the Palatinate, I'm finished!"

    show prussia intense

    p "Fortunately, my armies are mobilized..."

    p "But look at you, Bavaria. You're a mess. Austria is completely tied down wrestling with Hungary. She can't send a single Hussar to save you."

    show prussia smug

    p "It seems you need my help."

    show bavaria frustrated

    b "I would rather drink stagnant Rhine water than owe you a favor!"

    p "And this is what I get for treating you that one time? Suit yourself..."

    "Prussia pretends to inspect her perfectly polished military boots."

    show bavaria drunk

    b "Grrr... fine! Fine! March your stupid army in there and fix it!"

    show prussia joyful

    p "I thought you'd never ask."

    scene black with fade
    "A few weeks later... The Rhenish Palatinate."

    scene bg field
    show prussia intense at left
    show bavaria sad at left_side_sprite
    with dissolve

    "Prussia's armies, commanded by General Moritz von Hirschfeld, sweep through the Palatinate with terrifying, mechanical efficiency."

    play sound "sfx/artillery.ogg"
    with hpunch

    p "Target the barricades at Kaiserslautern! Do not give them a moment to breathe!"

    "The rebel forces, mostly poorly trained militia and romantic university students, are entirely outmatched."

    show bavaria normal

    b "You... you cleared the entire region in weeks. It's almost unnatural."

    show prussia smug

    show bavaria embarrassed

    "By the end of June, the uprising is entirely crushed."

    "She owes you some political favors..."

    jump turn_start

label rel_1849_baden:

    scene bg prussia office
    with fade

    "For the second time in barely a year, the Grand Duchy of Baden has completely collapsed."
    "Unlike the Hecker Rebellion, which was mostly romantic poets and students, this time is different. The actual Baden state military has mutinied, joined the radical democrats, and forced the Grand Duke to flee the country in the dead of night."

    show baden sad at center
    with hpunch

    bw "They took Karlsruhe! They took the armories! My own royal guards chased me out of the palace!"

    show baden frustrated

    bw "Prussia, you have to help me! It's an absolute disaster! They've declared a republic and barricaded themselves in the Rastatt fortress!"

    show prussia frustrated at right
    show baden sad at left
    with move

    p "Do I look like your personal maid?" 
    p "Do I exist to sweep up your messes every time a liberal coughs in your general direction?"

    show baden embarrassed

    bw "...No, but..."

    show prussia intense
    with vpunch

    p "Because I am currently dealing with the Palatinate!" 
    p "I am very, very tired of marching my infantry across the entire Confederation for you!"

    show baden sad

    bw "I know! I know I'm useless! But France is watching from across the Rhine!" 
    bw "If the revolution holds, France will use it as an excuse to cross the border!" 
    bw "You're the only one with the military strength to defeat a federal fortress!"

    "You pause. The mention of France crossing the Rhine immediately silences your complaints."

    show prussia normal

    p "They're holding Rastatt?"

    bw "Yes, with heavily armed defectors." 
    bw "It's not a militia anymore, it's a real army."

    show prussia smug

    p "Hehe. A fair fight."

    scene black with fade
    "July 1849. The Siege of Rastatt."

    scene bg rastatt
    with fade
    play sound "sfx/heavy_artillery.wav" loop

    "The fighting in Baden is some of the most brutal of the entire revolutionary period."

    "Unlike the street brawls of Berlin or Dresden, this is a conventional war, with Prussian artillery pounding the fortress of Rastatt day and night."

    stop sound
    scene bg karlsruhe palace
    with fade

    "However, by July the rebellion is entirely crushed. The leaders are court-martialed and executed by Prussian firing squads."

    show baden embarrassed at left
    show prussia normal at right
    with dissolve

    bw "You... you really did it. The Grand Duke is returning tomorrow."

    show baden sad

    bw "There's so much damage, though. So many dead."

    show prussia smug

    p "Look on the bright side. Your army is entirely destroyed, which means you get to rebuild it using Prussian drill instructors, Prussian rifles, and Prussian doctrine."

    show baden embarrassed

    bw "I suppose I don't really have a choice anymore, do I?" 

    bw "My state is practically a Prussian garrison now."

    p "Exactly. And as long as my troops are here, France won't dare take a single step across the Rhine."

    "Baden looks at you with a complicated mix of absolute terror and deep, profound gratitude."

    show baden joyful

    bw "Thank you, Prussia. Even if you are scary... you're the only one who actually protects me."

    show prussia joyful

    p "Just remember this the next time Austria asks for your vote in the Diet."

    jump turn_start